      "source": [
        "Z-Score\n",
        "\n",
        "The Z-score method identifies outliers based on the number of standard deviations a value is from the mean. Observations with |Z| > 3 are considered outliers.\n",
        "\n",
        "IQR\n",
        "\n",
        "The IQR method identifies outliers using the interquartile range. Values below Q1 − 1.5×IQR or above Q3 + 1.5×IQR are treated as outliers.\n",
        "\n",
        "Percentile\n",
        "\n",
        "The Percentile method removes or caps values below the 1st percentile and above the 99th percentile to reduce the influence of extreme values.\n",
        "\n",
        "Winsorization\n",
        "\n",
        "Winsorization replaces extreme values with the nearest acceptable percentile values instead of removing them, preserving the number of observations."
      ]
    },
